<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-675-006  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 675 006.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  July 23 1990 v7 n29 p17(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Epson ships low-cost scanner, high-resolution ink-jet printer.andO;(Epson America Inc.'s EPI-4000) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sexton, Tara.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Epson America Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Epson EPI-4000 (Computer printer) (product introduction)Epson ES-300C (Scanning device) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionInk-Jet PrintersScanning DevicesLow CostHigh Resolution.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Tara SextonandM;Epson America Inc. last week unveiled a low-cost desktop scanner and anink-jet printer that company officials said features high-resolution outputcomparable to that of laser technology.andM;The EPI-4000 ink-jet printer incorporates Epson's 64-nozzle printer head forresolutions of 300 by 300 dots per inch (dpi) on plain paper as large as 11by 17 inches, according to Peter Bergman, director of Epson's printerbusiness unit.andP;  The flexibility of paper formats will allow engineers andgraphics professionals to use the EPI-4000 as an alternative to a printer andplotter for CAD/CAE applications, he said.andM;Printing at 2 pages per minute, the $1,999 printer features a Motorola 68000processor, 512K bytes of RAM, a parallel port, serial port and a built-inpaper tray with automatic feed.andP;  Options include a 2M-byte memory board andEpson's black-ink cartridge with a character life of approximately 1,000pages.andM;Epson also introduced a $1,995 color/monochrome image scanner that boastsfaster image processing and greater accuracy of registration than comparablypriced desktop scanners, Bergman claimed.andM;For high-resolution images, the ES-300C uses 8-bit monochrome processing toproduce 256 shades of gray and 24-bit color processing to yield 16.8 millionhues with 300 dpi, he said.andM;The color-scanning mechanism features alternating red, blue and green lightbars that scan each line of the image and separate the colors simultaneouslyto process more accurate images faster, he explained.andM;In monochrome mode, the scanner emits a pure white light that captures theentire gray-scale spectrum, minimizing color dropout for better detail, hesaid.andM;Both the EPI-4000 and the ES-300C are available now.andM;Epson America Inc., of Torrance, Calif., can be reached at (213) 539-9140.andO;</TEXT></DOC>